"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `sns.set_style()` function. According to the seaborn documentation, the `rc` argument should be used to pass a dictionary of parameters to `axes_style()` and `set_style()`. However, the parameters in the dictionary should be part of the style definition. The parameter 'grid.color' is not part of the style definition and should be passed to the higher-level `set_theme()` function instead.\",\n  \"patch\": \"14c14\\n<sns.set_style(rc=style_dict)\\n---\\n>sns.set_theme(style='whitegrid', rc=style_dict)\"\n}"